BASKETBALL - PANATHINAIKOS SIGNS NBA VETERAN BYRON SCOTT . Former European basketball champions Panathinaikos signed on Thursday veteran NBA player Byron Scott in an effort to revamp the club ' s fortunes after a bad season . Panathinaikos officials said they paid $ 1 . 5 million to sign the 1 . 93 - metre forward who last played for Vancouver . Scott , 36 , has won three NBA titles with the Los Angeles Lakers in 1985 , 1987 and 1988 and has played more than 1 , 200 matches in the NBA . Panathinaikos , the most expensive club in Europe , won the Euroleague championship in 1996 led by NBA star Dominique Wilkins . But this year they only managed to win participation in the Korac Cup . 
